 Msobomvu - Msobomvu police have opened an inquest docket after a six-year-old boy drowned at Magqudwana Dam near Zizamele Township, in Butterworth, on Friday morning. "East London police divers were called to the scene and retrieved the body of the deceased on Friday afternoon," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "Police are warning children not to swim alone without supervision of the elders. "The identity of the deceased is still being withheld until all his relatives are officially informed of his death." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 